<tr>
<td>
<table class="infobox vevent" style="float: right; clear: right; width: 315px; border-spacing: 2px; text-align: left; font-size: 90%;">
<tr>
<th class="summary" colspan="2" style="background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; font-size: 110%;">World War&#160;II</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-size: 90%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa; line-height: 1.5em;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG" class="image"><img alt="Infobox collage for WWII.PNG" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG/300px-Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG" width="300" height="358" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/54/Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG/450px-Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/54/Infobox_collage_for_WWII.PNG 2x" /></a><br />
Clockwise from top left: Chinese forces in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Wanjialing" title="Battle of Wanjialing">Battle of Wanjialing</a>, Australian 25-pounder guns during the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/First_Battle_of_El_Alamein" title="First Battle of El Alamein">First Battle of El Alamein</a>, German <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Junkers_Ju_87" title="Junkers Ju 87">Stuka</a> dive bombers on the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eastern_Front_(World_War_II)" title="Eastern Front (World War II)">Eastern Front</a> winter 1943–1944, US&#160;naval force in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invasion_of_Lingayen_Gulf" title="Invasion of Lingayen Gulf">Lingayen Gulf</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wilhelm_Keitel" title="Wilhelm Keitel">Wilhelm Keitel</a> signing the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_Instrument_of_Surrender" title="German Instrument of Surrender">German Instrument of Surrender</a>, Soviet troops in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Stalingrad" title="Battle of Stalingrad">Battle of Stalingrad</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2">
<table style="width:100%; margin:0; padding:0; border:0">
<tr>
<th style="padding-right:1em">Date</th>
<td>1&#160;September&#160;1939<span style="display:none">&#160;(<span class="bday dtstart published updated">1939-09-01</span>)</span>&#160;– 2&#160;September&#160;1945<span style="display:none">&#160;(<span class="dtend">1945-09-02</span>)</span> (<span style="display:none" class="sortkey">7000600000000000000</span>6&#160;years, <span style="display:none" class="sortkey">7000100000000000000</span>1&#160;day)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding-right:1em">Location</th>
<td><span class="location"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Theatre_of_World_War_II" title="European Theatre of World War II" class="mw-redirect">Europe</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pacific_War" title="Pacific War">Pacific</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_Atlantic_(1939–1945)" title="Battle of the Atlantic (1939–1945)" class="mw-redirect">Atlantic</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South-East_Asian_Theatre_of_World_War_II" title="South-East Asian Theatre of World War II" class="mw-redirect">South-East Asia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Sino-Japanese_War" title="Second Sino-Japanese War">China</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediterranean,_Middle_East_and_African_theatres_of_World_War_II" title="Mediterranean, Middle East and African theatres of World War II" class="mw-redirect">Middle East</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediterranean,_Middle_East_and_African_theatres_of_World_War_II" title="Mediterranean, Middle East and African theatres of World War II" class="mw-redirect">Mediterranean</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediterranean,_Middle_East_and_African_theatres_of_World_War_II" title="Mediterranean, Middle East and African theatres of World War II" class="mw-redirect">Africa</a>, briefly <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Theater_(1939–1945)" title="American Theater (1939–1945)" class="mw-redirect">North</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_the_River_Plate" title="Battle of the River Plate">South America</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="padding-right:1em">Result</th>
<td><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allies_of_World_War_II" title="Allies of World War II">Allied</a> victory<br />
<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allied_occupation_of_Germany" title="Allied occupation of Germany" class="mw-redirect">Allied occupation of Germany</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occupation_of_Austria" title="Occupation of Austria" class="mw-redirect">Austria</a> (1945-1955)</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expulsion_of_Germans_after_World_War_II" title="Expulsion of Germans after World War II" class="mw-redirect">Expulsion of Germans from Eastern Europe</a></li>
<li>Allied occupation of Italy (1943-1947)</li>
<li>Formation of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Communist" title="Communist" class="mw-redirect">Communist</a> governments in Eastern Europe</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occupation_of_Japan" title="Occupation of Japan">U.S. occupation of Japan</a> (1945-1952)</li>
<li>Creation of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a><br /></li>
<li>Emergence of the <a href="United_States.html" title="United States">United States</a> and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Union" title="Soviet Union">Soviet Union</a> as <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Superpower" title="Superpower">superpowers</a><br /></li>
<li>Beginning of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cold_War" title="Cold War">Cold War</a> (<a href="World_War_II.html#Aftermath" title="World War II">more...</a>).</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
