<li id="cite_note-Kolko_1990_45-212"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Kolko_1990_45_212-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFKolko1990">Kolko 1990</a>, p.&#160;45: "On September 3, as Allied forces landed in Italy, Badoglio agreed to a secret armistice in the hope the Allies would land a major force north of Rome and save his government and the king. When he learned such a rescue would not occur he desperately attempted to call off his bargain with Eisenhower, who cut short the matter on September 8 by announcing news of its existence. The next day the hero of Abyssinia, his king, and a small retinue deserted Rome for the southeast tip of Italy, leaving most of Italy to the Nazis."</span></li>
