<li id="cite_note-389"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-389">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.idsia.ch/~juergen/zuse.html">"Konrad Zuse (1910–1995)"</a>. Istituto Dalle Molle di Studi sull'Intelligenza Artificiale<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 14 November 2009</span>. "Konrad Zuse builds Z1, world's first programme-controlled computer. Despite mechanical engineering problems it had all the basic ingredients of modern machines, using the binary system and today's standard separation of storage and control. Zuse's 1936 patent application (Z23139/GMD Nr. 005/021) also suggests a von Neumann architecture (re-invented in 1945) with programme and data modifiable in storage"</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWorld+War+II&amp;rft.btitle=Konrad+Zuse+%281910%E2%80%931995%29&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.idsia.ch%2F~juergen%2Fzuse.html&amp;rft.pub=Istituto+Dalle+Molle+di+Studi+sull%27Intelligenza+Artificiale&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
